body: The error means the C++ server tries to parse the message but did not see a legitimate end of the message (by checking `ConsumedEntireMessage` after parsing). Your trace seems like you have a 22B proto request and the trace seems fine. Is it possible that the client and server are not using the same proto file?

>  Is it possible that the client and server are not using the same proto file?

Agh! Thats exactly it!

> Is it possible that the client and server are not using the same proto file?

I closed this issue too early. Unfortunately this was not the issue. 

I have doubled checked several times. And have even checked protos in c++ project and python project using Beyond Compare - they are identical.
I have the same promble and for sure the proto file is same with vimdiff. But get the same Error Message : "rpc error: code = Internal desc = Did not read entire message " :(
